🌟 Reflecting on 2023 🌟 

As the curtain falls on another year, I can’t help but  look back and appreciate the whirlwind that was 2023.

👶 **New Beginnings**: Welcoming my second son into the world in February was the highlight of this year. The sleepless nights with a newborn and a lively 2-year-old brought challenges, but the joy they add to my life is immeasurable. 🍼👨‍👩‍👦‍👦 
 📚 **Pen to Paper**: Amidst diaper changes and lullabies, I managed to pen down my second international book  which will soon sit on bookshelves worldwide. A testament to the power of determination and late-night writing sessions. 📖💫 
 🚀 **Fortune 40 Under 40**: Grateful and humbled to be listed among the Fortune 40 Under 40. This recognition serves as a reminder that hard work, passion, and a dash of resilience can propel you to remarkable heights. 🚀🌐
 🏆 **Double Triumph with Houzz Awards**: Our company, High Q Renders, managed this year to receive not one, but two Houzz Awards! Each project is a labor of love, and these awards fuel our passion to create spaces that inspire. 🏡✨ 
 🎨 **CGArchitect 3D Awards**: Stepping into the role of a judge for the CGArchitect 3D Awards was an enriching experience. Witnessing the creativity and innovation in the world of 3D design was truly inspiring. 🖥️🌐

Balancing the roles of a mama and a professional has been an ongoing challenge as there never seem to be enough hours, but parenthood has added a new dimension to my life, filled with joy, love, and the sweetest chaos. Here’s to a new chapter and to new challenges. 🚀✨ 

#YearInReview #Reflections #Gratitude #NewBeginnings #LifeBalancingAct
